== Description ==
{{Blurimage|file=LuminusVSReD.jpg|align=right|hovertext=Omg ReDCosmic VS Extraluminus!!1!1!!1!1!1 (real) (emotional)|caption=A photography of a '''R.E.D.''' H.20 on a therapy room within [[Level 986]].}}
'''Object 30''', colloquially known as "'''Retractable Entity Detectors'''," or simply abbreviated as "'''R.E.D.'''s," are very rare objects in [[Backrooms Wiki|the Backrooms]]. '''R.E.D.''' appears as plastic, retractable tube-like structures with LEDs inside. The top, non-retractable part of the device has a white plate on its uppermost point; the top also contains a darkened button, which changes the '''R.E.D.'''<nowiki/>'s mode. Despite their acronym, '''R.E.D.'''s are actually yellow-colored. On the lower part of the device is a hole that allows for one to store small objects inside the device. This hole proves that '''R.E.D.s''' are hollow; the LEDs in them are seen from the hole. When pressing the dark button previously mentioned, the '''R.E.D.''' will change modes; it has three modes. The first is "Quick Twinkle."  In this mode, the '''R.E.D.'''<nowiki/>'s LEDs turn on and off rapidly. The second mode is "Slow Twinkle."  In this mode, the '''R.E.D.'''<nowiki/>'s LEDs turn on and off more slowly. The third mode is "Perpetual Light." In this mode, the LEDs only turn off manually. Despite its name, the '''R.E.D.'''<nowiki/>'s usage shifted with time; originally, the device's purpose became analyzing entities. Scientists renovated '''R.E.D.'''s and created a remote application that analyzes the entity detected by the device. Its LED lights were given a new function: a ray that scans the entity's information, such as vitals. The information is sent to the application and has helped researchers and biologists learn more about entities.

The original usage of the device was more simple: the LEDs would detect an entity, and once an entity was detected, the '''R.E.D.''' would begin glowing depending on its current mode. The LEDs would detect the entities by analyzing and comparing a human and another life form's information, distinguishing the human from the entity. This older variation of the device, named "'''R.E.D.''' H.20," can be found on levels, unlike the modern device, named "'''R.E.D.''' L.V.L.," which is obscure and kept secret. H.20 appears to be smaller than L.V.L., as it has fewer features and its LEDs only execute one task. H.20 stands for "Heap 20," inspired by the device's inventor's surname. Meanwhile, L.V.L. formerly stood for "Leap Volume Loud." The name was given as a joke by one of the projectors due to the loud noise that was produced while and after scanning an entity. Currently, L.V.L. stands for "Learn Validation of Life," due to the massive scientific discoveries due to L.V.L. and the validation of the lives of the entities, as entities are not murdered or injured during '''R.E.D.''' L.V.L.'s scan.

{{Blurimage|align=left|hovertext=Most bri'isher ahh bo'el|file=Wa'erdrOp UK.jpg|caption=One the hundreds of designs for '''R.E.D.''' H.20 W Int. Specifically, the most popular design, named "Bottle-20."}}

It is believed that '''R.E.D.s''' have a toy-like appearance to trick less intelligent, irrational entities, as they will appear more friendly and unaggressive. If the device had a more modern appearance, entities would know to destroy it. In order to convince entities better, a sticker taken from a similar, non-detecting item in [[the Frontrooms]] was put into the devices. This technique is exceedingly useful for irrational entities; however, intelligent entities can easily find out that the item is a '''R.E.D.''' Due to this, researchers developed a design for explorers when dealing with more intelligent entities. This design, known as "H.20 W Int," appears as a robust recreation of a metal bottle, with the top part appearing as a cap and the hole for storage being unexistent. This design is useful for newly discovered entities and levels. Although several of the entities that have been detected by the device have been seen to realize the trick, due to this, new designs are created monthly to continue the research.

During [[Phenomenon 12|the Flicker]], '''R.E.D.s''' became an extremely desired item, and wanderers and groups were desperately and mindlessly procuring these devices. Those who didn't have the devices were much more likely to die. '''R.E.D.s''' were overvalued and very expensive due to their rarity and utility, making it very difficult to gain them. The devices would be sold and donated to small, yet uncommon, tents in small quantities, randomly scattered around [[Backrooms Wiki|the Backrooms]]. These tents have disappeared, and their locations were vandalized and destroyed. '''R.E.D.s''' were given on first aid kits and at donation centers. It was on [[Phenomenon 12|the Flicker]] when '''R.E.D.''' L.V.L. and '''R.E.D.''' H.20 W Int were first invented, so people could learn new ways to defeat entities and research them independently of intelligence. The data collected from the remote L.V.L. application was well-used to research and protect wanderers during [[Phenomenon 12|the Flicker]], and to this day, the information is still used by hundreds of people who use this data weekly for research.

In 2021, scientists responsible for '''R.E.D.''' L.V.L. and H.20 W Int attempted to create artificial intelligence, which would be put into a new '''R.E.D.''' A.I.R., which stands for "Artificial Intelligence Runner." A.I.R. appears as a retractable red cube with a foldable screen. This artificial intelligence was an enormous failure, which caused a myriad of wanderers to murder and commit various mistakes. The inventors decided to remove and destroy all instances of '''R.E.D.''' A.I.R., and any remaining hidden A.I.R. instances and software were deactivated permanently. Several months later, developers recreated A.I.R. with more data, and some instances could have a moving body. These instances quickly drifted from their original purpose and were trained to destroy everything. It is believed that the developers wanted to attack groups with these A.I.R.s. Groups quickly saw what was happening and began planning to capture these developers. As of now, the instances were dismantled, but the developers were never captured or encountered.

== Usage ==
'''R.E.D.''' H.20 and H.20 W Int are used by wanderers and explorers when situated on dangerous levels with a myriad of entities to know when to run or protect themselves. '''R.E.D.''' L.V.L. is used by researchers to analyze an entity's information, such as their vitals, heart beat, mood, breathing, stress, and previously eaten food, among other information. Unlike '''R.E.D.''' H.20 and '''R.E.D.''' L.V.L., '''R.E.D.''' H.20 W Int may be used for both H.20 and L.V.L.'s purposes; however, H.20 W Int is more appropriate for H.20. Due to this, researchers are currently developing '''R.E.D.''' L.V.L. W Int, a variation of L.V.L., which will more efficiently scan intelligent entities, possibly causing a scientific breakthrough. '''R.E.D.''' H.20 may also be used physically against entities, as the LED lights may be used to damage the entity's vision, as they are stronger and brighter than the ordinary LED lights.

== Locations ==
These devices are extremely rare, and '''R.E.D.''' H.20 is only encountered on modern, industrial, machine-related, or generally technological levels, inside closets, lying on desks and chairs, and on crates and high-tech safes. '''R.E.D.''' L.V.L.'s location is obfuscated, created in laboratories by specialized researchers, and cannot be naturally found. '''R.E.D.''' L.V.L. is unallowed to be used by non-explorers, non-militarists, and non-researchers, and usage of it by regular citizens is strictly forbidden and will result in imprisonment for two weeks according to the [[Backrooms Wiki|Backrooms]]-wise '''R.E.D.''' monitoring and controlling treaty. Some of the main locations where '''R.E.D.s''' are encountered are [[Level 986]], [[Level 92]], [[Level 594]], [[Level 2]], and [[Level 464]], among other similar levels.

== Discovery ==
'''R.E.D.s''' (specifically H.20.) were discovered on [[Level 986]]; they were first sighted lying by desks and beds. Initially, the discoverers did not know much information regarding the objects. They ultimately wanted to hold more knowledge on these devices, therefore launching many explorations to encounter them. After the explorers discovered its usage, the devices were massively wanted and desired. '''R.E.D.s''' have been remade, redesigned, and very much used ever since their discovery. '''R.E.D.''' L.V.L. and '''R.E.D.''' H.20 W Int were developed and designed by researchers in laboratories at, presumably, [[Level 92]], [[Level 986]], and/or [[Level 464]]. The two devices were specifically created for research and safety purposes, respectively.</div></div></div>
